---
import SectionHeading from '../ui/SectionHeading.astro';
import HonestyNote from '../ui/HonestyNote.astro';
---

<section class="gb-section" data-galaxy-state="nebula" aria-labelledby="roadmap-title">
	<div class="gb-container">
		<SectionHeading
			kicker="What we won't pretend"
			title="The honest roadmap."
			lede="Marketing pages usually hide this part. We think the gaps are as load-bearing as the features — here is exactly where the engine is still being built."
			id="roadmap-title"
		/>
		<div class="gb-roadmap-list">
			<HonestyNote title="Postgres update/delete on the new plane is in flight.">
				The Rust data plane serves list/get/insert on all engines today; the remaining Postgres write
				verbs ship behind the same shadow→parity→cutover gates as everything else.
			</HonestyNote>
			<HonestyNote title="OLAP/OLTP cost-routing is partial.">
				Trino analytics is reachable, but as its own endpoint — the unified "point-reads hit the engine,
				analytics hit the lakehouse, automatically" plane is the roadmap's centrepiece, not today's reality.
			</HonestyNote>
			<HonestyNote title="No billing layer yet.">
				Capability masks and rate limits are enforced live; metering, quotas and invoicing are still to come.
			</HonestyNote>
			<HonestyNote title="Single-node today.">
				The stack is Docker-Compose-first; HA and horizontal scale (Helm/K8s) are a later phase. Most
				tenants on most tiers genuinely don't need them yet — see the measured footprints.
			</HonestyNote>
			<HonestyNote title="8 engines, not 20.">
				DreamFactory connects more systems. We'd rather grow the adapter list one honest, capability-typed
				engine at a time than advertise breadth we can't gate.
			</HonestyNote>
		</div>
	</div>
</section>
